==English==
===Etymology===
From [[Bordeaux]] in France, where it is used on vines
===Noun===
'''[[Bordeaux]] [[mixture]]'''
# a mixture of [[copper sulphate]] and [[lime]] that is sprayed on plants as a [[fungicide]]
===Quotations===
*'''1891''' Reports are coming to hand from a very large number of districts as to the success which has attended the use of the '''Bordeaux mixture''' (sulphate of copper and lime) as a preventive of potato disease. ''The Times'' Nov 16, 1891 pg 12 col A''